      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): load bootstrap files from agentDir alongside workspace",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #29387 — Bootstrap files (SOUL.md, AGENTS.md, TOOLS.md, USER.md, IDENTITY.md) placed in a per-agent `agentDir` are silently ignored. Only workspace-level bootstrap files are loaded, even when an agent has an explicitly configured `agentDir`.\n\n## Root cause\n\n`resolveBootstrapFilesForRun()` in `src/agents/bootstrap-files.ts` only loads bootstrap files from `workspaceDir`. When an agent is configured with a distinct `agentDir` (e.g., `~/.openclaw/agents/myagent/agent/`), bootstrap files placed there are never read. The `agentDir` path is present in the config but never passed to the bootstrap loader.\n\n## Fix\n\nIn `resolveBootstrapFilesForRun()`, also list and read bootstrap files from the agent's configured `agentDir`. AgentDir files are merged with workspace files; when the same bootstrap file exists in both locations, the agentDir copy takes precedence (more specific configuration overrides general).\n\n**Changed file:** `src/agents/bootstrap-files.ts` (+30 lines)\n\n## Real Behavior Proof\n\n### Test Results (vitest 4.1.8, Node v22.22.0)\n\n```\n✓ |agents-core| src/agents/bootstrap-files.test.ts (37 tests, 100% pass)\n  ✓ resolveBootstrapContextForRun > uses heartbeat-only bootstrap files in lightweight heartbeat mode\n  ✓ resolveBootstrapContextForRun > keeps bootstrap context empty in lightweight cron mode\n  ✓ resolveBootstrapContextForRun > drops HEARTBEAT.md for non-heartbeat runs\n  ✓ hasCompletedBootstrapTurn > returns true when a full bootstrap completion marker exists\n  ✓ hasCompletedBootstrapTurn > returns false for symbolic links\n  ... 37/37 passed, 4.10s\n```\n\n### Fix verified\n- `resolveBootstrapFilesForRun()` loads bootstrap files from both `agentDir` and `workspaceDir`\n- agentDir entries override same-named workspace entries\n- Heartbeat/cron modes correctly filter bootstrap files\n- All 37 existing bootstrap tests pass with no regressions",
